According to a Samsung executive, the electronics company is working on a foldable display for its laptops, The Korea Herald reported. Lee Min-cheol, Samsung vice president of marketing for PCs, said, “Samsung is collaborating with display makers to develop laptops with foldable displays that will not just simply fold in and out but create new value and user experience, amid the changing market trends for laptops.” Samsung is currently working with panel makers to develop large AMOLED displays for laptops, he added. He said this in Seoul, Korea, during a showcase event for Samsung’s latest Flash laptop. The new Flash laptop incorporates Intel‘s newest wireless LAN card for a faster internet experience, which features faster Internet speeds.